1
00:00:04,982 --> 00:00:08,266
This month’s expenses are
higher than the jobs we can take on.

2
00:00:08,733 --> 00:00:11,100
Maybe Mr. Tohr could help us.

3
00:00:11,400 --> 00:00:14,300
For the Petchprakai Troupe,
you'll have my full support.

4
00:00:15,566 --> 00:00:16,866
What are you doing?

5
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:18,933
There’s no artistry in this at all.

6
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:20,866
This doesn’t feel like home anymore.

7
00:00:21,266 --> 00:00:23,066
It feels more like a company chasing targets.

8
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:24,733
About the job Mr. Tohr just took—

9
00:00:25,066 --> 00:00:26,066
He took it for three hundred and fifty thousand.

10
00:00:26,133 --> 00:00:27,733
Then why did he tell P’Phet it was
just three hundred thousand?

11
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:29,966
Maybe Mr. Tohr isn’t actually taking advantage of us.

12
00:00:30,266 --> 00:00:31,600
I love this place like it’s home.

13
00:00:32,333 --> 00:00:34,133
But if no one trusts each other here,

14
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:35,566
then it’s not home anymore.

15
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,666
Just let me go my own way.

16
00:00:51,566 --> 00:00:53,566
Hello, Khun Headman.

17
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:56,166
I’ve got good news.

18
00:00:57,100 --> 00:01:00,766
This year, our village fair is coming back.

19
00:01:03,266 --> 00:01:05,611
So I want your Petchprakai Troupe

20
00:01:06,323 --> 00:01:08,376
to open the show for the whole village.

21
00:01:09,241 --> 00:01:12,146
The whole village has been waiting for your troupe.

22
00:01:12,655 --> 00:01:13,808
So I didn’t wait.

23
00:01:14,419 --> 00:01:17,133
I brought the deposit and contract myself.

24
00:01:17,533 --> 00:01:18,333
Here it is.

25
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:23,272
I know your troupe’s been getting a lot of work lately.

26
00:01:23,832 --> 00:01:26,846
So I came early before your schedule fills up.

27
00:01:27,660 --> 00:01:29,722
I want to see our village stage

28
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,630
filled with Likay again.

29
00:01:32,088 --> 00:01:33,678
Your Likay performances

30
00:01:33,678 --> 00:01:36,900
bring joy to the whole village.

31
00:01:40,933 --> 00:01:42,933
Thank you very much, Headman.

32
00:01:45,266 --> 00:01:46,242
But—

33
00:01:47,412 --> 00:01:49,673
right now, the Petchprakai Troupe,

34
00:01:50,733 --> 00:01:51,725
the performers,

35
00:01:53,506 --> 00:01:54,854
aren’t all here.

36
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:58,983
I thought so.

37
00:01:59,492 --> 00:02:02,121
The house felt unusually quiet today.

38
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:07,024
Pleng Chai went out.

39
00:02:07,024 --> 00:02:08,100
He hasn’t come back yet.

40
00:02:12,100 --> 00:02:14,600
He’s been gone for days, hasn’t he?

41
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:20,100
This isn’t a small matter anymore.

42
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:22,766
It’s alright, my boy Phet Thae.

43
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:26,700
I believe you'll all definitely
come back as a full troupe again.

44
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,345
The Petchprakai Troupe—

45
00:02:30,599 --> 00:02:31,342
just the name

46
00:02:31,698 --> 00:02:33,634
is already the village’s hope.

47
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:36,727
I’ll get going now.

48
00:02:37,694 --> 00:02:39,281
Please think about the fair.

49
00:02:40,254 --> 00:02:42,861
I really want to see you on stage again.

50
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:45,500
Thank you very much.

51
00:03:03,733 --> 00:03:05,200
My troupe leader

52
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:07,100
is already capable.

53
00:03:09,733 --> 00:03:11,400
As the troupe leader’s partner,

54
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,133
I’ll help out too.

55
00:04:58,300 --> 00:04:59,500
I can’t find anything.

56
00:05:01,066 --> 00:05:02,266
There’s not even a café.

57
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:04,966
Where did he go?

58
00:05:21,566 --> 00:05:22,871
Hello.

59
00:05:23,075 --> 00:05:25,070
This is the Heart Connection Service Center.

60
00:05:25,666 --> 00:05:28,066
You have an outstanding balance.

61
00:05:28,333 --> 00:05:30,478
Please make the payment within 24 hours.

62
00:05:30,478 --> 00:05:33,566
Otherwise, your connection will be cut off.

63
00:05:34,166 --> 00:05:36,331
Huh? What?

64
00:05:36,789 --> 00:05:38,184
I never signed up for this.

65
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:39,987
Hey—

66
00:05:40,292 --> 00:05:41,600
are you trying to scam me
into extending my love plan?

67
00:05:41,933 --> 00:05:43,133
I don’t have money to pay.

68
00:05:45,733 --> 00:05:47,366
But if I can pay with my heart,

69
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:49,266
just say the word.

70
00:05:50,766 --> 00:05:52,466
If you want to continue the connection,

71
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:53,500
press one.

72
00:05:53,733 --> 00:05:55,100
If you want to end the connection,

73
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:56,733
please hang up.

74
00:05:57,300 --> 00:05:58,100
Oh—

75
00:05:58,200 --> 00:05:59,566
then I’ll just hang up.

76
00:06:00,166 --> 00:06:00,966
So I don’t have to pay in installments.

77
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:02,133
Interest on love like this—

78
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:03,100
Ow, ow—

79
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:04,333
just kidding.

80
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,166
I just called because I was worried.

81
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:09,766
Wait—hold on—

82
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:11,800
that voice…

83
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,133
is that Lynchee?

84
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:17,266
Did you call to mess with me?

85
00:06:17,966 --> 00:06:18,766
Hmm?

86
00:06:19,366 --> 00:06:21,333
I just wanted to hear your voice.

87
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:23,700
I thought you might be stressed,

88
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:26,366
so I called to tease you a bit.

89
00:06:27,133 --> 00:06:28,266
So you’d laugh.

90
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:30,200
Be honest—

91
00:06:30,866 --> 00:06:32,500
were you worried, or teasing more?

92
00:06:34,533 --> 00:06:36,791
Still, thanks.

93
00:06:37,758 --> 00:06:40,366
You relieve my stress better than any doctor.

94
00:06:41,933 --> 00:06:43,029
That’s good.

95
00:06:43,283 --> 00:06:45,554
Just hearing you laugh is enough for me.

96
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:49,800
Thanks.

97
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:54,786
But today, I’m taking ten points off

98
00:06:55,142 --> 00:06:56,866
for running away from home.

99
00:06:58,766 --> 00:07:00,740
Alright, I’ll give you five back.

100
00:07:01,656 --> 00:07:02,733
Because you answered my call.

101
00:07:03,733 --> 00:07:06,333
Even if my score drops,

102
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:09,500
at least I got your scammer number.

103
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:11,300
That’s worth it.

104
00:07:50,133 --> 00:07:52,333
Okay, okay, that’s enough.

105
00:07:55,766 --> 00:07:56,796
The more I practice,

106
00:07:57,050 --> 00:07:59,187
the more out of sync I feel with my body.

107
00:08:02,966 --> 00:08:05,076
So that’s why

108
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:08,548
Mr. Tohr always has to handle bookings.

109
00:08:08,802 --> 00:08:13,991
I wonder if the troupe would survive without him.

110
00:08:14,966 --> 00:08:16,300
I brought you some food.

111
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,012
P’Phet,

112
00:08:22,012 --> 00:08:23,366
I’ll go eat first.

113
00:08:25,166 --> 00:08:28,284
Then I’ll go check the choreography
and the new song.

114
00:08:28,284 --> 00:08:30,066
Maybe it’ll start to feel more natural.

115
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:31,800
Sure.

116
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:41,200
What should we do, P’Phet?

117
00:08:42,733 --> 00:08:44,500
But what she said,

118
00:08:46,266 --> 00:08:47,733
it’s worth thinking about, Ploy.

119
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:55,533
Sometimes it’s not wrong to rely on Mr. Tohr.

120
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:59,100
But if we keep letting others see us like this,

121
00:09:00,066 --> 00:09:02,066
We’ll never truly feel confident in ourselves.

122
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:04,853
Yeah.

123
00:09:07,754 --> 00:09:09,183
I want everyone to see it too.

124
00:09:09,437 --> 00:09:11,798
That our troupe can move forward

125
00:09:12,103 --> 00:09:13,416
on our own.

126
00:09:14,179 --> 00:09:16,871
Not because someone’s pulling us along.

127
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:19,278
Then,

128
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:22,130
we should talk to Mr. Tohr first.

129
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:24,400
Today.

130
00:09:25,533 --> 00:09:27,700
Before that vendor comes again.

131
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:30,800
Alright.

132
00:09:31,666 --> 00:09:34,566
Then let’s go talk to him now.

133
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:37,105
It’s time to prove it.

134
00:09:37,105 --> 00:09:40,180
That our troupe can move forward

135
00:09:40,485 --> 00:09:42,171
on our own.

136
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:44,133
Yes, boss.

137
00:09:44,933 --> 00:09:45,760
Let’s go.

138
00:09:46,421 --> 00:09:47,673
Vice leader.

139
00:09:55,166 --> 00:09:55,966
Mr. Tohr.

140
00:09:56,733 --> 00:09:57,966
Oh, what is it?

141
00:10:00,533 --> 00:10:04,266
Today, I’d like to talk about something personal,
not work.

142
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:07,733
Hmm, you look serious.

143
00:10:08,300 --> 00:10:09,600
Alright, go on.

144
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:15,242
We really have to thank you, Mr. Tohr.

145
00:10:15,242 --> 00:10:19,534
Without your help, Mr. Tohr,
we wouldn’t have gotten work like this.

146
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,336
Mr. Tohr, you…

147
00:10:21,743 --> 00:10:24,706
could be known as a top Likay manager

148
00:10:24,706 --> 00:10:26,227
without a doubt.

149
00:10:28,066 --> 00:10:30,800
I’d say I’m more of a silver-tongued manager.

150
00:10:31,700 --> 00:10:33,800
Say one word, and people give in.

151
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,400
That’s true, Mr. Tohr.

152
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:42,488
But…

153
00:10:42,488 --> 00:10:44,457
Right now, we feel that

154
00:10:44,864 --> 00:10:49,249
we want to try running the troupe ourselves.

155
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:59,733
We want it to grow by our own hands.

156
00:11:01,466 --> 00:11:02,644
As for everything before,

157
00:11:04,018 --> 00:11:05,900
we’re truly grateful to you.

158
00:11:05,966 --> 00:11:06,766
That’s alright.

159
00:11:07,866 --> 00:11:08,666
Sigh.

160
00:11:10,366 --> 00:11:12,766
That really makes me feel good.

161
00:11:14,133 --> 00:11:16,025
It makes me feel like

162
00:11:16,025 --> 00:11:17,878
our Petchprakai Troupe

163
00:11:18,234 --> 00:11:19,922
can go even further.

164
00:11:22,300 --> 00:11:25,342
If you’re free, please come watch our show sometime.

165
00:11:25,342 --> 00:11:28,533
I’ll save you a front-row seat.

166
00:11:29,700 --> 00:11:30,589
Of course.

167
00:11:30,945 --> 00:11:34,122
I’ll cheer until I lose all my voice,
isn't it alright?

168
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:36,505
(Ploy Ying) Sounds great.
(Phet Thae) Thank you so much, Mr. Tohr.

169
00:11:37,167 --> 00:11:38,966
If anything comes up,

170
00:11:39,933 --> 00:11:41,200
and we need help again,

171
00:11:41,900 --> 00:11:45,466
I’ll definitely come back to you.

172
00:11:46,166 --> 00:11:46,966
Anytime, my boy.

173
00:11:47,933 --> 00:11:49,447
My door

174
00:11:49,447 --> 00:11:51,254
is always open for you.

175
00:11:51,763 --> 00:11:53,075
No need to be shy.

176
00:11:53,838 --> 00:11:55,843
Just think of it as your home.

177
00:11:56,454 --> 00:11:57,253
You know,

178
00:11:57,507 --> 00:11:59,979
when I first joined a Likay troupe,

179
00:12:00,691 --> 00:12:02,559
no one helped me.

180
00:12:03,366 --> 00:12:05,266
The reason I’m still standing here is

181
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:08,066
it’s not because of fame,

182
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:11,533
but because of the people in the troupe—

183
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,866
because they trust each other.

184
00:12:17,533 --> 00:12:19,056
And if one day

185
00:12:19,056 --> 00:12:20,632
we have to face hardship,

186
00:12:21,650 --> 00:12:22,979
remember my words well.

187
00:12:24,099 --> 00:12:25,471
People of Likay

188
00:12:25,929 --> 00:12:27,471
must fight with heart.

189
00:12:27,776 --> 00:12:31,471
If you still love the stage

190
00:12:32,533 --> 00:12:34,266
and still believe in your own voice,

191
00:12:35,133 --> 00:12:36,452
then there’s no one

192
00:12:36,452 --> 00:12:38,300
who can put out your light.

193
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:41,664
Yes, sir.

194
00:12:42,834 --> 00:12:44,183
I’ll remember that.

195
00:12:44,997 --> 00:12:46,028
Our troupe

196
00:12:46,435 --> 00:12:49,100
will never let that light fade again.

197
00:12:50,300 --> 00:12:53,466
Good. That suits the name Phet Thae.

198
00:12:54,366 --> 00:12:57,912
A true gem must fight to shine, my boy.

199
00:13:01,300 --> 00:13:05,300
It’s time to dust off the stage and make it shine again.

200
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:14,889
Hello.

201
00:13:15,856 --> 00:13:16,439
What’s up?

202
00:13:17,508 --> 00:13:19,000
You called because you miss me, right?

203
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:21,286
No way.

204
00:13:21,286 --> 00:13:23,037
I’m calling to tell you something.

205
00:13:24,207 --> 00:13:25,615
Mr. Tohr has left the troupe.

206
00:13:27,866 --> 00:13:30,266
What? Really?

207
00:13:31,533 --> 00:13:35,069
Yeah, P’Phet and Mr. Tohr talked it out properly.

208
00:13:35,069 --> 00:13:37,666
They said they want to try managing things on their own.

209
00:13:39,333 --> 00:13:40,571
But more importantly,

210
00:13:40,571 --> 00:13:42,982
they ask about you every day.

211
00:13:43,491 --> 00:13:44,971
How’s Pleng doing?

212
00:13:44,971 --> 00:13:46,789
Has he eaten yet?

213
00:13:46,789 --> 00:13:49,155
I hear it so much I feel full just hearing it.

214
00:13:54,366 --> 00:13:56,166
So P’Phet isn’t mad at me anymore?

215
00:13:57,300 --> 00:13:58,881
He’s not mad anymore.

216
00:13:58,881 --> 00:14:01,089
P’Ploy still asks about you every day.

217
00:14:01,089 --> 00:14:03,666
She said if you call, try asking him to come back.

218
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:14,200
Yeah, yeah.

219
00:14:15,666 --> 00:14:16,933
Let me think about it first.

220
00:14:49,166 --> 00:14:50,100
What are you doing?

221
00:14:50,966 --> 00:14:52,966
You scared me, Lynchee.

222
00:14:53,566 --> 00:14:54,722
What are you doing?

223
00:14:54,722 --> 00:14:55,222
Nothing.

224
00:14:56,266 --> 00:14:57,066
Nothing.

225
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:01,800
Hey.

226
00:15:03,166 --> 00:15:04,166
That’s all wrong.

227
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:06,300
Your teacher’s going to deduct a lot of points.

228
00:15:09,456 --> 00:15:10,409
You okay?

229
00:15:24,666 --> 00:15:25,664
You didn’t sleep,

230
00:15:26,224 --> 00:15:27,864
you went to work part-time, right?

231
00:15:31,933 --> 00:15:34,000
Now you’re looking for a new place

232
00:15:34,666 --> 00:15:36,500
because you don’t want to bother P’Nine.

233
00:15:38,366 --> 00:15:39,900
If I’m not mistaken,

234
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,333
you’re having money problems, right?

235
00:15:45,933 --> 00:15:46,800
How did you know?

236
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:48,700
Are you a detective or something?

237
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,400
I just observed,

238
00:15:53,166 --> 00:15:53,966
thought,

239
00:15:53,966 --> 00:15:55,566
and analyzed what I saw.

240
00:15:56,766 --> 00:15:58,000
Look at your eye bags.

241
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:00,200
They’re dark like a panda.

242
00:16:03,866 --> 00:16:04,666
A panda?

243
00:16:05,533 --> 00:16:06,900
So that means I’m cute, right?

244
00:16:10,700 --> 00:16:11,733
I’m being serious.

245
00:16:12,700 --> 00:16:13,500
I want to help you.

246
00:16:20,466 --> 00:16:21,688
Daddy,

247
00:16:24,639 --> 00:16:26,026
what you said earlier

248
00:16:26,280 --> 00:16:28,599
about how much you love the Petchprakai Troupe,

249
00:16:29,209 --> 00:16:31,069
how much do you really love them?

250
00:16:34,900 --> 00:16:35,993
Very much.

251
00:16:36,705 --> 00:16:39,539
I’m a real patron of the troupe.

252
00:16:40,404 --> 00:16:42,823
I’ve been following them since the older generation.

253
00:16:43,739 --> 00:16:46,124
I remember who played which role.

254
00:16:46,124 --> 00:16:48,077
I love everyone in the troupe.

255
00:16:48,891 --> 00:16:50,000
But…

256
00:16:50,966 --> 00:16:53,335
Why are you suddenly asking about this?

257
00:16:53,895 --> 00:16:55,607
Even though before,

258
00:16:55,607 --> 00:16:57,849
when I took you there, you kept complaining.

259
00:16:58,700 --> 00:17:03,700
If you hadn’t told me, I wouldn’t have known
you’re such a big patron of the troupe.

260
00:17:05,933 --> 00:17:08,666
It’s just like how you’re a fan of K-pop.

261
00:17:13,366 --> 00:17:14,454
So,

262
00:17:16,082 --> 00:17:19,307
what do you think about P’Pleng?

263
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:29,333
He’s naturally good-looking.

264
00:17:30,733 --> 00:17:31,766
He knows how to get by.

265
00:17:32,666 --> 00:17:34,466
But he parties a bit too much.

266
00:17:35,366 --> 00:17:36,666
He never really sticks to anything.

267
00:17:37,933 --> 00:17:39,318
But lately,

268
00:17:40,387 --> 00:17:42,721
I’ve seen him going out saying he’s going to classes.

269
00:17:42,721 --> 00:17:44,252
I’m still wondering.

270
00:17:44,252 --> 00:17:45,030
what’s the reason?

271
00:17:48,966 --> 00:17:50,300
Because of me.

272
00:17:52,133 --> 00:17:54,766
I want him to have a future.

273
00:17:55,066 --> 00:17:57,733
If he’s going to come after me,

274
00:18:03,900 --> 00:18:04,702
That’s good then.

275
00:18:05,465 --> 00:18:07,431
If you love someone, I’ll love them too.

276
00:18:08,166 --> 00:18:08,966
I do love him.

277
00:18:10,133 --> 00:18:13,974
But these days, money is really hard to come by.

278
00:18:13,974 --> 00:18:15,166
Will you be able to handle it?

279
00:18:27,966 --> 00:18:29,366
I want to help pay for your tuition.

280
00:18:31,133 --> 00:18:32,933
It’s okay, Lynchee. Really.

281
00:18:34,533 --> 00:18:35,177
No.

282
00:18:35,177 --> 00:18:36,877
I’m not giving it to you for free.

283
00:18:36,877 --> 00:18:38,679
You’ll still have to pay me back in installments anyway.

284
00:18:38,679 --> 00:18:42,466
I’ve already prepared a contract—here, take a look.

285
00:18:47,933 --> 00:18:48,866
A contract like this?

286
00:18:49,866 --> 00:18:50,666
Why?

287
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:52,300
Is there a zero-interest installment plan?

288
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:54,766
Yes, there is.

289
00:18:55,466 --> 00:18:58,000
But you have to take me out for dessert every week.

290
00:19:01,666 --> 00:19:03,133
This bank’s brutal.

291
00:19:04,733 --> 00:19:05,533
Not yet.

292
00:19:05,866 --> 00:19:07,600
This is already the kind version.

293
00:19:08,533 --> 00:19:09,566
If it were really strict,

294
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:11,466
the moment you miss a payment,

295
00:19:11,566 --> 00:19:13,366
I’ll wipe out all your points.

296
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:24,592
Let me think about it first.

297
00:19:25,610 --> 00:19:26,709
Actually,

298
00:19:27,829 --> 00:19:29,250
I don’t really want to borrow money from anyone.

299
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,337
Hmm.

300
00:19:33,271 --> 00:19:35,187
Then,

301
00:19:36,866 --> 00:19:37,915
you should just go back home.

302
00:19:54,166 --> 00:19:55,487
I’m going to class now.

303
00:19:55,487 --> 00:19:56,300
Hey—

304
00:20:01,566 --> 00:20:02,591
Oops.

305
00:20:03,405 --> 00:20:05,943
What did you get out of fighting with
your family and walking out?

306
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:09,133
I’ve seen it.

307
00:20:09,866 --> 00:20:12,533
You keep secretly checking the troupe’s
TikTok all the time.

308
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:16,200
Stop being stubborn and just go back home.

309
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:22,800
I’m going to class now.

310
00:20:25,366 --> 00:20:26,166
I’ll go with you.

311
00:21:03,166 --> 00:21:04,900
Is the Petchprakai Troupe going live?

312
00:21:12,666 --> 00:21:13,466
Oh!

313
00:21:13,700 --> 00:21:15,600
This mic keeps acting up on P’Phet every day.

314
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:17,000
Hey—

315
00:21:17,666 --> 00:21:19,533
Man, if Pleng were here,

316
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,966
he’d fix it in five minutes.

317
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:30,613
That Pleng guy,

318
00:21:30,969 --> 00:21:32,847
he’s a key part of the troupe.

319
00:21:33,407 --> 00:21:35,756
When he’s not here, everything falls apart.

320
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,779
Honestly,

321
00:21:38,779 --> 00:21:42,566
if Pleng were still here,
the troupe would be a lot more fun.

322
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:44,800
Huh.

323
00:21:45,366 --> 00:21:46,666
You miss me that much?

324
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:49,566
(Phet Thae) When do I get to sing?
(Pleng Chai) This troupe, huh,

325
00:21:50,266 --> 00:21:51,693
it wouldn’t survive without me, huh?

326
00:21:51,693 --> 00:21:52,526
Can you fix it?

327
00:21:52,966 --> 00:21:53,766
Nope.

328
00:21:54,566 --> 00:21:55,466
Careful, it might short out.

329
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:56,566
Start from here first.

330
00:21:56,800 --> 00:21:57,600
This one?

331
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:58,400
That’s right.

332
00:22:00,133 --> 00:22:00,933
Alright.
(Phet Thae) Does it work?

333
00:22:02,566 --> 00:22:04,400
Since you miss me that much,

334
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:10,100
it’s time for
a handsome clown hero like me

335
00:22:10,700 --> 00:22:12,200
to come back.

336
00:22:45,933 --> 00:22:46,700
Wow.

337
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,166
The food looks really delicious.

338
00:22:49,766 --> 00:22:50,566
Come on,

339
00:22:50,866 --> 00:22:51,968
let’s eat.

340
00:22:51,968 --> 00:22:52,468
Sure.

341
00:22:58,266 --> 00:22:59,376
Hey, you,

342
00:22:59,376 --> 00:23:01,700
so what’s going on with Pleng Chai?

343
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:11,157
Oh, Pleng,

344
00:23:12,277 --> 00:23:14,133
are you really going back home?

345
00:23:14,566 --> 00:23:15,080
Yes.

346
00:23:15,385 --> 00:23:16,398
I’m heading back now.

347
00:23:17,133 --> 00:23:18,307
I’ve thought it through.

348
00:23:18,612 --> 00:23:19,497
I think…

349
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:21,611
I’m not upset with P’Phet and P’Ploy anymore.

350
00:23:22,366 --> 00:23:23,666
If I stay here too long,

351
00:23:23,766 --> 00:23:25,466
they’ll miss me too much.

352
00:23:25,966 --> 00:23:26,766
Hmm?

353
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:29,333
So where are you going next?

354
00:23:30,733 --> 00:23:32,400
I’ve got to go back and help at the troupe,

355
00:23:32,654 --> 00:23:33,850
and finish my studies as soon as possible.

356
00:23:34,966 --> 00:23:36,309
Oh, P’Nine,

357
00:23:36,309 --> 00:23:36,866
I…

358
00:23:38,466 --> 00:23:39,625
thank you so much

359
00:23:39,625 --> 00:23:41,837
for letting me stay and for the utilities.

360
00:23:41,837 --> 00:23:43,058
When I get the chance,

361
00:23:43,058 --> 00:23:44,705
I’ll pay you back right away.

362
00:23:45,367 --> 00:23:47,957
Please take care of my friend too.

363
00:23:48,766 --> 00:23:50,917
Don’t worry about that.

364
00:23:51,222 --> 00:23:52,971
I’m rooting for you, keep fighting.

365
00:23:53,100 --> 00:23:53,900
Thank you.

366
00:23:57,066 --> 00:23:59,600
What about you, aren’t you going back home?

367
00:24:03,533 --> 00:24:05,300
If I don’t succeed, I don’t want to go back.

368
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:08,100
I need a bit more time for myself.

369
00:24:09,366 --> 00:24:10,466
I want to make it.

370
00:24:11,300 --> 00:24:12,533
Only then will I have the courage to go back.

371
00:24:26,533 --> 00:24:28,111
Everyone has their own path,

372
00:24:29,536 --> 00:24:30,373
and I

373
00:24:31,187 --> 00:24:33,453
am still walking on the path of that dream.

374
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:46,800
Just saying “I love you”

375
00:24:47,966 --> 00:24:49,533
why is it so difficult?

376
00:24:54,466 --> 00:24:56,566
And how do I keep eye contact without breaking?

377
00:25:05,066 --> 00:25:07,996
Are you practicing your lines?

378
00:25:07,996 --> 00:25:09,592
Mr. rising star actor.

379
00:25:10,661 --> 00:25:11,667
When did you get here?

380
00:25:12,888 --> 00:25:17,242
Since the moment you said “I love you,”

381
00:25:18,266 --> 00:25:20,066
and turned red like a tomato.

382
00:25:22,533 --> 00:25:24,533
It’s my first love scene.

383
00:25:24,933 --> 00:25:25,966
I’m not used to it yet.

384
00:25:34,066 --> 00:25:35,133
If that’s the case,

385
00:25:38,566 --> 00:25:39,700
want me to help?

386
00:25:41,733 --> 00:25:43,366
I’ll be your practice partner.

387
00:26:32,100 --> 00:26:32,900
So,

388
00:26:33,866 --> 00:26:36,200
do you understand love scenes better now?

389
00:26:39,866 --> 00:26:40,839
Yeah, I do.

390
00:26:43,335 --> 00:26:44,105
But…

391
00:26:44,767 --> 00:26:45,420
I think

392
00:26:47,303 --> 00:26:48,936
we might need to practice a bit more.

393
00:26:50,966 --> 00:26:51,673
Like…

394
00:26:53,505 --> 00:26:55,815
what do they do next?

395
00:26:59,366 --> 00:27:02,726
Are you teasing me?

396
00:27:03,947 --> 00:27:05,118
No.

397
00:27:06,441 --> 00:27:07,635
I just want to know.

398
00:27:08,398 --> 00:27:13,625
In case they add more love scenes in the series,

399
00:27:14,338 --> 00:27:15,838
I want to practice in advance.

400
00:27:30,933 --> 00:27:33,400
Then let’s try something else today.

401
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:41,333
How about we record something of
the two of us to watch in the future?

402
00:27:54,333 --> 00:27:55,133
Ready?

403
00:27:59,100 --> 00:28:02,800
Today is our first day of
practicing a love scene together.

404
00:28:03,566 --> 00:28:05,366
It’s our first love scene.

405
00:28:07,300 --> 00:28:08,720
And it turned out

406
00:28:09,687 --> 00:28:10,698
not bad at all.

407
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:21,202
It’s the day I realized

408
00:28:22,932 --> 00:28:24,646
real feelings

409
00:28:25,766 --> 00:28:26,860
and what’s in the script

410
00:28:28,030 --> 00:28:30,210
are actually so close.

411
00:28:45,866 --> 00:28:46,966
I miss home.

412
00:28:49,133 --> 00:28:50,533
I know I have to keep going.

413
00:28:52,300 --> 00:28:54,366
I want to go back with pride.

414
00:28:57,066 --> 00:28:58,400
not just in the series.

415
00:29:08,366 --> 00:29:10,333
Right now, you’re not alone anymore.

416
00:29:13,600 --> 00:29:15,166
You still have me by your side.

417
00:29:28,366 --> 00:29:29,523
Today,

418
00:29:31,304 --> 00:29:33,273
I’m lucky to have you beside me.

419
00:30:02,733 --> 00:30:03,600
Hello.

420
00:30:05,166 --> 00:30:07,500
Hey, Pleng Chai is really back.

421
00:30:48,266 --> 00:30:49,266
I’m sorry.

422
00:30:53,733 --> 00:30:54,635
that I…

423
00:30:55,093 --> 00:30:56,780
never really trusted you.

424
00:30:58,566 --> 00:30:59,913
I’m sorry too.

425
00:31:01,338 --> 00:31:03,145
If you can manage your time,

426
00:31:03,552 --> 00:31:05,466
come back and perform with the troupe again.

427
00:31:09,966 --> 00:31:11,079
I also

428
00:31:12,249 --> 00:31:13,517
want to apologize to you all.

429
00:31:14,789 --> 00:31:15,975
Back then, I

430
00:31:17,451 --> 00:31:19,156
was too hot-headed.

431
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:21,894
From now on, I won’t act like that again.

432
00:31:24,600 --> 00:31:25,400
Thank you.

433
00:31:29,466 --> 00:31:32,721
Thanks, Lynchee, for writing the script.

434
00:31:32,721 --> 00:31:34,311
I just followed the script.

435
00:31:34,311 --> 00:31:36,010
No problem at all.

436
00:31:36,264 --> 00:31:37,074
Ploy,

437
00:31:38,700 --> 00:31:39,766
you’re revealing it just like that?

438
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:44,861
I mean, I saw Pleng

439
00:31:44,861 --> 00:31:46,400
checking the troupe’s page all the time.

440
00:31:46,933 --> 00:31:48,100
sometimes you even accidentally liked posts.

441
00:31:48,533 --> 00:31:49,533
sometimes you pretended not to like them.

442
00:31:49,766 --> 00:31:52,066
So I set up a live to lure you back.

443
00:32:00,300 --> 00:32:02,075
Wait—hold on.

444
00:32:04,060 --> 00:32:06,802
So you set up a live to trick me?

445
00:32:08,200 --> 00:32:09,000
Not trick you.

446
00:32:10,700 --> 00:32:12,766
Just calling you back with heart, that’s all.

447
00:32:13,866 --> 00:32:14,794
Then tonight,

448
00:32:15,608 --> 00:32:17,268
can you check the sound system for me?

449
00:32:17,733 --> 00:32:21,166
The old one cuts in and out.

450
00:32:21,600 --> 00:32:22,866
Like it’s sulking at me.

451
00:32:29,966 --> 00:32:31,133
Sure, P’Phet.

452
00:32:31,744 --> 00:32:34,902
I’ll make it blast across the whole market.

453
00:32:36,366 --> 00:32:39,200
Now that you’re back, don’t run off again.

454
00:32:41,733 --> 00:32:42,866
Who would run?

455
00:32:43,933 --> 00:32:45,300
After baiting me like this?

456
00:32:45,766 --> 00:32:46,566
I’m not going anywhere.

457
00:32:54,100 --> 00:32:55,133
I don’t bite.

458
00:32:59,333 --> 00:33:00,200
Where have you been?

459
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:02,832
In Bangkok.

460
00:33:02,832 --> 00:33:04,766
(Pleng Chai) I went to Bangkok.
(Ploy Ying) Bangkok?

461
00:33:13,300 --> 00:33:14,866
P’Phet, let’s go eat.

462
00:33:16,933 --> 00:33:17,866
Let’s go eat.

463
00:33:30,366 --> 00:33:31,620
It’s all behind us now.

464
00:33:32,536 --> 00:33:33,969
At least now,

465
00:33:34,376 --> 00:33:36,354
things are starting to fall into place.

466
00:33:38,133 --> 00:33:39,666
And we’ve paid off a lot of debt too.

467
00:33:45,266 --> 00:33:46,664
Stay strong with me.

468
00:33:46,664 --> 00:33:47,657
Ploy.

469
00:33:49,387 --> 00:33:50,780
Fighting alone is lonely.

470
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:01,200
Wow.

471
00:34:01,700 --> 00:34:03,500
Today’s full of surprises.

472
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:05,066
P’Phet,

473
00:34:05,566 --> 00:34:07,266
you can act sweet too?

474
00:34:08,500 --> 00:34:09,700
You’ve changed a lot.

475
00:34:15,600 --> 00:34:17,123
And if one day

476
00:34:18,293 --> 00:34:20,301
you have to stand on stage alone,

477
00:34:26,966 --> 00:34:28,566
you’d be so lonely, wouldn’t you?

478
00:34:29,400 --> 00:34:30,266
If everyone’s gone,

479
00:34:32,800 --> 00:34:33,866
especially you, Ploy,

480
00:34:39,900 --> 00:34:43,133
as long as you’re here, I’m not afraid of anything.

481
00:34:47,733 --> 00:34:49,103
Let’s get back to work.

482
00:34:50,273 --> 00:34:51,721
Vice leader,

483
00:34:52,586 --> 00:34:54,157
don’t slack off.

484
00:34:55,900 --> 00:34:56,700
Yes.

485
00:35:09,200 --> 00:35:10,066
P’Phet,

486
00:35:12,966 --> 00:35:15,766
I think it’s time now.

487
00:35:17,933 --> 00:35:21,366
I want to work more behind the scenes.

488
00:35:25,166 --> 00:35:26,200
What do you mean?

489
00:35:27,333 --> 00:35:28,700
Are you going to stop performing?

490
00:35:31,300 --> 00:35:32,100
I’m not quitting.

491
00:35:32,966 --> 00:35:34,600
But after what happened with Mr. Tohr,

492
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:37,319
I’ve thought it through,

493
00:35:38,082 --> 00:35:42,821
I’ve thought it through, P’Phet.
I want to help manage the troupe more seriously.

494
00:35:43,839 --> 00:35:46,643
Since we have Pleng helping now,

495
00:35:47,305 --> 00:35:50,701
you’ll have time to train new performers.

496
00:36:01,400 --> 00:36:03,533
But I don’t want a new heroine yet.

497
00:36:05,100 --> 00:36:08,533
I want you to always be my heroine.

498
00:36:11,266 --> 00:36:12,466
What I mean is,

499
00:36:13,100 --> 00:36:14,933
we can create a new pair.

500
00:36:18,733 --> 00:36:19,871
As for me,

501
00:36:21,194 --> 00:36:23,719
I still want to be your heroine forever.

502
00:36:29,700 --> 00:36:30,887
Hearing you say that,

503
00:36:33,228 --> 00:36:35,213
it makes me think of Guy.

504
00:36:40,933 --> 00:36:42,162
P’Phet,

505
00:36:42,773 --> 00:36:44,608
don’t overthink it.

506
00:36:45,219 --> 00:36:48,289
Now I understand,

507
00:36:48,747 --> 00:36:50,645
that the most important thing

508
00:36:51,408 --> 00:36:53,421
is seeing you and Guy

509
00:36:53,777 --> 00:36:55,355
finally talk things out.

510
00:38:06,100 --> 00:38:07,294
You’re awake?

511
00:38:07,752 --> 00:38:10,482
Let’s eat together, I made food.

512
00:38:11,800 --> 00:38:13,133
And congratulations,

513
00:38:13,733 --> 00:38:15,500
our first series together

514
00:38:15,900 --> 00:38:17,000
is getting great feedback.

515
00:38:18,766 --> 00:38:19,566
Thank you.

516
00:38:21,700 --> 00:38:22,875
Do you know,

517
00:38:23,791 --> 00:38:25,408
since I grew up,

518
00:38:26,528 --> 00:38:29,600
aside from my family,
no one has ever cooked for me.

519
00:38:30,821 --> 00:38:32,068
You’re the first.

520
00:38:35,800 --> 00:38:37,201
If that’s the case,

521
00:38:37,557 --> 00:38:39,348
then stay with me for a long time.

522
00:38:39,348 --> 00:38:42,020
I’ll cook for you every day.

523
00:38:42,529 --> 00:38:44,556
But not as a father.

524
00:39:08,066 --> 00:39:08,866
Alright.

525
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:15,000
Let’s be together.

526
00:39:52,333 --> 00:39:53,251
Sometimes,

527
00:39:54,065 --> 00:39:56,470
love doesn’t need many words.

528
00:39:58,455 --> 00:39:59,839
Just knowing that…

529
00:40:00,399 --> 00:40:01,522
we choose each other,

530
00:40:02,336 --> 00:40:04,104
and stay by each other’s side is enough.

531
00:41:05,700 --> 00:41:07,560
Wow, P’Phet,

532
00:41:08,883 --> 00:41:11,003
you’re taking such good care of the costume.

533
00:41:13,566 --> 00:41:15,143
Of course, I have to.

534
00:41:15,957 --> 00:41:17,266
It’s expensive.

535
00:41:20,700 --> 00:41:21,688
Or is it

536
00:41:21,993 --> 00:41:25,238
that you miss the person who wore it more?

537
00:41:29,100 --> 00:41:30,700
I’m just taking care of the costume.

538
00:41:31,366 --> 00:41:32,166
Hmph.

539
00:41:32,500 --> 00:41:33,900
Now you’re turning it on me.

540
00:41:37,100 --> 00:41:38,493
Honestly,

541
00:41:38,493 --> 00:41:40,527
I think the issue between you and Guy

542
00:41:40,527 --> 00:41:43,284
has been stuck in your heart for a long time.

543
00:41:44,046 --> 00:41:50,306
Don’t tell me you’ll fix it by taking care of clothes
instead of talking.

544
00:41:53,066 --> 00:41:56,599
I was thinking of taking care of ten outfits or so,

545
00:41:56,599 --> 00:42:00,566
maybe that’ll help me forget the resentment.

546
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:04,498
You can’t forget it like that.

547
00:42:04,905 --> 00:42:06,275
People,

548
00:42:06,275 --> 00:42:07,585
even if they don’t say anything,

549
00:42:07,941 --> 00:42:09,215
they still keep thinking about it.

550
00:42:11,066 --> 00:42:12,535
The difference is,

551
00:42:12,840 --> 00:42:15,081
some people keep it to themselves quietly,

552
00:42:15,488 --> 00:42:17,971
while others say it out loud.

553
00:42:19,900 --> 00:42:21,420
But I think you, Ploy,

554
00:42:21,980 --> 00:42:23,686
are starting to say it out loud too.

555
00:42:28,100 --> 00:42:29,364
If I don’t say it,

556
00:42:29,364 --> 00:42:32,536
you’d probably keep sewing all night like this.

557
00:42:32,892 --> 00:42:34,239
Honestly,

558
00:42:35,333 --> 00:42:37,117
even if I get to work behind the scenes,

559
00:42:37,575 --> 00:42:39,787
or have Pleng helping out,

560
00:42:40,666 --> 00:42:41,763
there’s one thing

561
00:42:41,763 --> 00:42:43,473
that I want to see the most.

562
00:42:44,185 --> 00:42:48,438
I want to see you and Guy talk normally

563
00:42:49,266 --> 00:42:50,675
without drama,

564
00:42:50,675 --> 00:42:52,425
without things blowing up,

565
00:42:53,137 --> 00:42:55,605
just talking normally is enough.

566
00:42:57,566 --> 00:42:58,733
You make it sound easy.

567
00:43:00,500 --> 00:43:01,044
Come on.

568
00:43:01,960 --> 00:43:03,070
It is easy.

569
00:43:04,200 --> 00:43:05,986
Just say,

570
00:43:06,953 --> 00:43:07,759
“Hey.”

571
00:43:08,064 --> 00:43:09,492
That’s enough.

572
00:43:09,492 --> 00:43:12,332
No need to apologize or explain.

573
00:43:12,332 --> 00:43:15,160
Just say “Hey,”

574
00:43:15,160 --> 00:43:16,905
just to get it started.

575
00:43:17,466 --> 00:43:19,533
What if Guy gives you a cold look?

576
00:43:19,966 --> 00:43:20,766
Come on.

577
00:43:21,533 --> 00:43:23,477
Then just add more words.

578
00:43:24,393 --> 00:43:26,342
“Hey, are you hungry?”

579
00:43:26,342 --> 00:43:30,275
Thai people can’t resist food.

580
00:43:32,500 --> 00:43:35,321
I think that’s interesting.

581
00:43:35,321 --> 00:43:38,733
That might work better than saying sorry.

582
00:43:39,333 --> 00:43:42,309
See? No need to be so serious.

583
00:43:44,395 --> 00:43:47,733
Family matters sometimes start with a lame joke.

584
00:43:47,987 --> 00:43:49,688
so the conversation can keep going.

585
00:43:57,566 --> 00:43:58,600
Thank you, Ploy.

586
00:44:00,733 --> 00:44:02,471
I think I should try that method.

587
00:44:03,285 --> 00:44:06,417
“Hey, are you hungry?”

588
00:44:07,231 --> 00:44:08,536
I’ll try it.

589
00:44:09,766 --> 00:44:11,825
This is the secret trick.

590
00:44:11,825 --> 00:44:14,929
If it works and makes Guy stop being mad at you,

591
00:44:14,929 --> 00:44:16,100
come tell me.

592
00:44:16,100 --> 00:44:19,789
I’ll sell this trick on TikTok.

593
00:44:20,298 --> 00:44:21,638
I’ll pin it in the cart.

594
00:44:22,733 --> 00:44:24,800
You’re such a business-minded person.

595
00:44:25,533 --> 00:44:26,333
Of course.

596
00:44:26,500 --> 00:44:27,300
If we love someone, we help them.

597
00:44:28,200 --> 00:44:29,533
When you’re rich, don’t forget me.

598
00:44:34,533 --> 00:44:35,333
Hey.

599
00:44:35,733 --> 00:44:36,533
Are you hungry?

600
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:38,300
Yeah, I am. Are you?

601
00:44:39,600 --> 00:44:40,400
Are you hungry?

602
00:44:40,933 --> 00:44:41,733
Not anymore.

603
00:44:42,600 --> 00:44:43,933
You eat all day and night.

604
00:44:52,666 --> 00:44:53,466
Hey,

605
00:44:53,600 --> 00:44:54,754
Hm.

606
00:44:54,754 --> 00:44:55,400
Look at this.

607
00:44:57,690 --> 00:45:00,271
“From a Likay hero to a rising male lead.”

608
00:45:00,933 --> 00:45:02,700
They wrote the headline like that?

609
00:45:04,666 --> 00:45:05,666
It’s kind of strange.

610
00:45:07,166 --> 00:45:08,413
But in another way,

611
00:45:08,413 --> 00:45:10,266
I think it’s a good thing, isn’t it?

612
00:45:10,666 --> 00:45:13,666
The more buzz there is, the more attention you get.

613
00:45:27,100 --> 00:45:28,236
Before,

614
00:45:28,999 --> 00:45:30,475
I thought that too.

615
00:45:33,733 --> 00:45:35,100
But thinking about it again,

616
00:45:37,933 --> 00:45:38,966
it’s really good.

617
00:45:40,466 --> 00:45:41,800
So good it’s confusing.

618
00:45:46,600 --> 00:45:48,800
Don’t overthink it.

619
00:45:49,666 --> 00:45:52,133
You really have a unique appeal.

620
00:45:52,866 --> 00:45:56,866
The studio is just trying to create buzz
to get people talking more.

621
00:46:00,200 --> 00:46:01,000
Thank you.

622
00:46:06,266 --> 00:46:07,879
Even though I should be happy,

623
00:46:09,304 --> 00:46:10,803
deep down,

624
00:46:11,617 --> 00:46:13,717
I find myself missing the Likay troupe again.

625
00:46:40,066 --> 00:46:41,292
Hello, Guy.

626
00:46:42,462 --> 00:46:44,220
Why are you calling all of a sudden?

627
00:46:44,700 --> 00:46:47,539
P’Ploy, how’s the troupe right now?

628
00:46:48,302 --> 00:46:49,756
Is everything okay?

629
00:46:51,700 --> 00:46:52,611
It’s fine.

630
00:46:53,629 --> 00:46:54,973
Don’t worry.

631
00:46:55,482 --> 00:46:57,022
Just focus on your work.

632
00:46:57,022 --> 00:46:58,290
As for things here,

633
00:46:58,697 --> 00:47:00,068
I’ll take care of it.

634
00:47:00,700 --> 00:47:01,462
P’Ploy,

635
00:47:02,734 --> 00:47:04,016
you sound tired.

636
00:47:05,644 --> 00:47:07,019
You should rest.

637
00:47:11,000 --> 00:47:12,400
I’m not that tired.

638
00:47:12,858 --> 00:47:15,482
Just a bit busy.

639
00:47:16,245 --> 00:47:17,170
Soon…

640
00:47:18,392 --> 00:47:19,533
I’ll get to rest.

641
00:47:50,300 --> 00:47:51,100
P’Ploy,

642
00:47:53,600 --> 00:47:54,400
Ploy,

643
00:47:56,100 --> 00:47:57,266
What’s wrong? You okay?

644
00:47:59,666 --> 00:48:00,800
I just feel dizzy.

645
00:48:02,733 --> 00:48:03,900
Maybe I didn’t sleep enough.

646
00:48:10,866 --> 00:48:11,666
Hey!

647
00:48:12,566 --> 00:48:13,366
Wait—

648
00:48:14,266 --> 00:48:15,333
Are you pregnant?

649
00:48:15,933 --> 00:48:17,466
You’ve been vomiting a lot lately.

650
00:48:19,166 --> 00:48:20,000
That must be it.

651
00:48:21,000 --> 00:48:21,866
Stop talking nonsense.

652
00:48:22,766 --> 00:48:23,566
Are you sure?

653
00:48:26,000 --> 00:48:26,966
Should we see a doctor?

654
00:48:32,562 --> 00:48:35,715
Nine-Guy just a shipped couple
or actually dating?

655
00:48:43,500 --> 00:48:44,766
Stop it already.

656
00:48:48,966 --> 00:48:50,650
Nine, Guy—

657
00:48:51,362 --> 00:48:54,178
Those off-screen photos of you both
are way too sweet.

658
00:48:54,890 --> 00:48:57,153
Some fans are not happy.

659
00:48:58,066 --> 00:49:00,300
We’re just living normally.

660
00:49:01,066 --> 00:49:02,866
We didn’t mean to make it news.

661
00:49:05,766 --> 00:49:06,666
From now on,

662
00:49:07,766 --> 00:49:09,766
keep the sweetness only for public events.

663
00:49:11,100 --> 00:49:11,900
Understand?

664
00:49:13,700 --> 00:49:15,666
Some people only like the pairing,

665
00:49:17,133 --> 00:49:17,933
not the real couple.

666
00:49:46,766 --> 00:49:50,200
Is this crispy pork basil from the usual place?

667
00:50:06,892 --> 00:50:07,570
Ploy really pregnant?

668
00:50:07,570 --> 00:50:08,806
For real, it’s everywhere right now

669
00:50:08,806 --> 00:50:09,467
She’s looked pale and sick a lot,could it be real?

670
00:50:09,467 --> 00:50:10,000
Or she’s just been working too hard?

671
00:50:10,000 --> 00:50:10,830
So who’s gonna replace the lead then?

672
00:50:10,830 --> 00:50:11,834
Who could possibly replace P’Ploy?

673
00:50:16,566 --> 00:50:17,680
P’Phet—

674
00:50:19,512 --> 00:50:21,117
I have something to tell you.

675
00:50:23,254 --> 00:50:25,694
Right now,

676
00:50:26,508 --> 00:50:28,474
people in the market are gossiping

677
00:50:30,000 --> 00:50:31,184
that P’Ploy

678
00:50:31,846 --> 00:50:34,252
is pregnant, that’s why she fainted.

679
00:50:40,366 --> 00:50:41,566
I’m sorry.

680
00:50:42,300 --> 00:50:43,700
I spoke carelessly.

681
00:50:45,133 --> 00:50:48,966
I didn’t think it would blow up like this.

682
00:50:53,366 --> 00:50:54,600
Speaking without thinking like that

683
00:50:55,666 --> 00:50:57,600
really hurts her, Pleng.

684
00:50:59,966 --> 00:51:00,933
And news like this,

685
00:51:01,466 --> 00:51:02,366
the one affected

686
00:51:03,066 --> 00:51:04,600
is only Ploy.

687
00:51:07,533 --> 00:51:09,346
I’m sorry again.

688
00:51:10,415 --> 00:51:11,571
It’s really my fault.

689
00:51:12,487 --> 00:51:15,297
I was just afraid that

690
00:51:15,297 --> 00:51:17,275
if P’Ploy heard it,

691
00:51:17,275 --> 00:51:19,273
she’d get even more stressed.

692
00:51:30,133 --> 00:51:30,933
Pregnant…

693
00:51:32,206 --> 00:51:34,355
They dare say that?

694
00:51:39,966 --> 00:51:40,766
Ploy—

695
00:51:41,466 --> 00:51:42,266
P’Ploy—

696
00:51:55,900 --> 00:51:57,091
Just now,

697
00:51:57,498 --> 00:52:01,507
I heard what you were talking about.

698
00:52:07,566 --> 00:52:08,300
Ploy—

699
00:52:08,707 --> 00:52:11,173
I don’t want you to overthink this.

700
00:52:15,900 --> 00:52:18,166
About them saying I’m pregnant?

701
00:52:20,700 --> 00:52:22,533
I’m not that weak.

702
00:52:24,333 --> 00:52:27,174
P’Ploy, I’m sorry.

703
00:52:27,836 --> 00:52:30,000
I should’ve handled it better.

704
00:52:30,533 --> 00:52:31,924
It’s okay, Pleng.

705
00:52:32,433 --> 00:52:34,171
It’s not your fault.

706
00:52:35,500 --> 00:52:36,800
People will gossip—

707
00:52:37,733 --> 00:52:39,466
it can’t be stopped.

708
00:52:50,300 --> 00:52:53,760
Lately it feels like heaven is sending tests

709
00:52:54,269 --> 00:52:55,651
for me again and again.

710
00:53:00,733 --> 00:53:02,866
Once I leave the hospital,

711
00:53:04,133 --> 00:53:07,400
I’ll go talk to the troupe members myself.

712
00:53:08,700 --> 00:53:10,666
So there won’t be more false rumors.

713
00:53:11,933 --> 00:53:14,319
And from now on,

714
00:53:14,624 --> 00:53:15,874
when we work,

715
00:53:16,637 --> 00:53:20,020
I’ll be more careful about our image.

716
00:53:20,133 --> 00:53:21,009
No, Ploy.

717
00:53:21,823 --> 00:53:24,136
Let me handle this.

718
00:53:26,800 --> 00:53:29,203
I won’t let anyone speak badly about you again.

719
00:53:31,364 --> 00:53:32,792
I love you, Ploy.

720
00:53:33,708 --> 00:53:36,311
And I believe the Petchprakai Troupe fans

721
00:53:36,565 --> 00:53:38,154
and everyone else

722
00:53:38,968 --> 00:53:40,474
if they know the truth

723
00:53:42,204 --> 00:53:44,779
no one will stand against us.

724
00:53:51,300 --> 00:53:52,700
Thank you, P’Phet.

725
00:53:56,066 --> 00:53:56,966
Don’t overthink it.

726
00:54:32,550 --> 00:54:33,991
#PetchTae and PloyYing

727
00:54:33,991 --> 00:54:34,922
#Petchprakai

728
00:54:34,922 --> 00:54:36,311
#TraditionalArtsGossip

729
00:54:43,240 --> 00:54:49,569
Ploy Ying Collapses Petch Tae Rushes
Her to the Hospital, Stays by her side

730
00:55:00,800 --> 00:55:01,700
(Pleang Chai) What the hell is it.
(Comment) Really?

731
00:55:01,700 --> 00:55:02,330
Is Ploy really pregnant?

732
00:55:02,330 --> 00:55:02,864
Petch Tae got Ploy Ying pregnant , just as the likay troupe was rising

733
00:55:02,864 --> 00:55:03,364
They still look so young

734
00:55:05,866 --> 00:55:06,883
Pregnant for real, or just gossip?

735
00:55:06,883 --> 00:55:07,560
What’s gonna happen to the troupe now?

736
00:55:07,560 --> 00:55:08,060
They were on the rise. Do they have to stop now

737
00:55:08,060 --> 00:55:08,839
Who’s stepping in for them, then?”

738
00:55:08,839 --> 00:55:09,567
No way P’Petch would do something like that

739
00:55:12,064 --> 00:55:13,682
P’Phet, have you seen the news?
It’s all over.

740
00:55:57,087 --> 00:55:59,180
♪ Rumors are like shadows ♪

741
00:56:00,000 --> 00:56:02,611
♪ that cover the heart ♪

742
00:56:03,832 --> 00:56:06,262
♪ Truth is a fire ♪

743
00:56:06,646 --> 00:56:08,660
♪ that shines through the dark ♪

744
00:56:12,700 --> 00:56:17,660
♪ The heart is never alone ♪

745
00:56:18,932 --> 00:56:22,406
♪ love stays by our side ♪

746
00:56:22,711 --> 00:56:24,535
♪ in moments of joy ♪

747
00:56:25,400 --> 00:56:27,767
♪ O truth, speak clear ♪

748
00:56:28,021 --> 00:56:30,471
♪ through words of verse ♪

749
00:56:31,234 --> 00:56:36,069
♪ love does not waver ♪

750
00:56:36,884 --> 00:56:41,225
♪ my dear ♪

751
00:56:41,966 --> 00:56:45,679
Khun Ploy Ying,
a member of the Petchprakai Troupe, is pregnant.

752
00:56:45,679 --> 00:56:47,400
Is this true?

753
00:56:48,066 --> 00:56:51,933
Today I’ll take you to face a Headman-level dungeon.

754
00:56:52,100 --> 00:56:54,466
What if I tell you to break up—
what would you do?

755
00:56:55,066 --> 00:56:56,960
We’ll let time prove it.

756
00:56:56,960 --> 00:56:59,100
Let people accept us.

757
00:57:01,333 --> 00:57:02,133
Who are you?

758
00:57:03,100 --> 00:57:03,933
You lied to me.

759
00:57:04,266 --> 00:57:05,133
What is going on?
